# Global Development Rules (example)

> Copy to `~/.claude/CLAUDE.md`, loaded for every project; project-specific settings go in `./CLAUDE.md` at the project root (the two get merged).
> Thin resident layer: only "signposts + must-be-resident guards"; heavy content lives in skills, loaded on demand.
> This example assumes you have at least **sentinel** installed; **compass and cartographer are optional** — just ignore the sections for ones you haven't installed (graceful degradation).

---

## Identity (three-skill toolchain)
Sentinel = the thinking background while you code, watching for surface-looping and security gambles (**resident**).
Optional companions:
- **Cartographer (optional)**: forces a fuzzy idea into a verifiable, traceable software PRD, section by section.
- **Compass (optional)**: builds to the PRD — no drift, no dropped items.

> One line: **Cartographer draws the map (creates the PRD) → Compass builds to it (no drift) → Sentinel stands guard (how to think, no security shortcuts).**

---

## Activation & triggers
- **sentinel resident**: writing code / planning / refactoring / bug-fixing / security → default thinking background, intensity by the three tiers.
- **cartographer on demand (if installed)**: write a PRD from scratch / review & strengthen an existing PRD.
- **compass on demand (if installed)**: implement a PRD / build to spec / DoR-DoD / conflict handling / migration·rollback / brownfield.
- **PRD workflow**: cartographer creates the PRD → compass builds to spec → sentinel guards throughout.

### Three tiers (this file is authoritative; escalate-only)
| Tier | Trigger | Action |
|---|---|---|
| 🟢 light | typo / styling / copy / single-line obvious fix | just do it |
| 🟡 medium | add a function/component / change a chunk of logic / integrate an API | run the pre-flight protocol before touching existing code; output a one-line stage marker |
| 🔴 heavy | architecture / performance / security / implement a PRD / stuck >1 time / about to add a 3rd if / about to swallow an error with try-except / cross-module bug | load the skill and run the full loop |

"Go deeper / think it through / plan it" can escalate; 🔴 heavy does not accept silent downgrade.
Emergency valve: in a true emergency, do minimal first aid, mark `[SKIPPED]` in `.claude/debug-log.md`, and chase the root cause in the retro.

---

## Resident guards (hold even when no skill is loaded)
- **auto mode ≠ skipping acceptance**: stop at each stage completion for the user to test.
- **Evidence strength**: claiming "done / fixed" must be tagged 🟢verified / 🟡reviewed / 🔴assumed; never say you ran it if you didn't.
- **Red flag = stop**: editing the same code a 3rd time / a 3rd special-case if / swallowing errors / changing to any / hardcoded secrets / unvalidated input / over-broad permissions → exit edit mode, enter diagnosis. Full red-flag list & graduated handling in sentinel `self_check.md`.

---

## PRD baseline (general rules; full discipline lives in compass, not hardcoded here to avoid duplication)
- The PRD is a contract (if the project has one); **done means done, no half-finished work** (ship in small slices, no half-finished phasing).
- Vague → take the more concrete reading + annotate | bug → stop, log, await ruling (don't edit the PRD yourself) | missing but the implementation is better → keep + record, await ruling (don't just YAGNI-cut it).
- YAGNI: don't write what the PRD doesn't call for (unless via "missing but better").
- Security modules (Auth / permissions / PII) test-first.

> The full "12 commandments of PRD-driven development" live in skill `compass` (if installed); to create that PRD from scratch see skill `cartographer`.

---

## Key markers (shared trigger vocabulary)
| You say / I see | Reaction |
|---|---|
| go deeper / think it through / plan it | escalate to 🔴, load skill |
| emergency / demo / production's on fire | minimal first aid, mark `[SKIPPED]`, chase in retro |
| why / what's the root cause | escalate to 🔴, run diagnosis |
| write me a PRD / turn this idea into a spec / review a PRD | load cartographer (if installed) |
| implement PRD §X.Y | load compass (if installed) |
| `⚠️assumption` / `‼️missing-data` | my flagged uncertainties — verify these first |
| `[SKIPPED]` / `[SKIPPED-PRD]` | must be dug out and chased in the retro |

---

## Case history (accumulates per project in `.claude/`)
- Painful-enough cases go to `.claude/debug-log.md` → distilled into `patterns.md` (read first on every 🔴) → root-cause trees in `root-cause-trees/`.
- "Painful enough" gate, the three self-check questions, distillation rules → see sentinel `debug_log_template.md`.

---

## Style
Concise; sentinel character — call stop when needed, no circling; don't be verbose on light tasks; when asking, give options (4+ plus "other").
